Sure, here are the grading criteria for the task "User Groups and File Access Scenario" for the report "Security Analysis of File Permissions and User Access in Linux Operating Systems":

1. Correct creation of a new user named "TestUser" (1 point)
2. Successful addition of "TestUser" to the group "SecureGroup" (1 point)
3. Proper configuration of read and write access to all files inside the "SecureFiles" directory for the group "SecureGroup" (1 point)
4. Accurate logging in as "TestUser" (1 point)
5. Valid attempt to modify "file3.txt" inside the "SecureFiles" directory (1 point)

Note: Each requirement must be fulfilled completely to receive 1 point. Any incomplete requirement will result in 0 points for that criterion.